message.entry: Allow the two inputs to differ in size (Results in variable-size output signal)

The signal dimensions of the first and second input ports of Manual Switch block ''{0}'' are different. To support a variable-size output signal, on the block dialog, select the parameter "Allow different data input sizes (Results in variable-size output signal)".
Manual Switch block must be placed in a model or unlocked library in order to operate.
The parameter 'Action' can only take character vector "0" or "1".
The parameter 'CurrentSetting' can only take character vector "0" or "1".
